# Testing Rules

## Backend (Jest)
- Test files co-located with source: `module-name.spec.ts`
- Unit test services by mocking repository/dependencies
- Use `Test.createTestingModule()` for NestJS testing utilities
- Test controllers with supertest for integration tests
- Name tests: `describe('ServiceName')` -> `it('should do X when Y')`

## Frontend (Vitest)
- Test files co-located: `ComponentName.spec.tsx`
- Use React Testing Library for component tests
- Test user interactions, not implementation details
- Mock API calls with MSW (Mock Service Worker)
- Mock Socket.IO events for real-time feature tests

## Coverage
- Aim for 80%+ coverage on services and critical business logic
- Don't test trivial getters/setters or framework boilerplate
- Always test error paths and edge cases

## Naming
```
describe('AuthService', () => {
  describe('verifyCode', () => {
    it('should return JWT tokens for valid code', () => {});
    it('should throw BadRequestException for expired code', () => {});
    it('should enforce rate limit after 5 failures', () => {});
  });
});
```
